cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.ST, cs.IT, cs.SI 

The paper presents a novel approach to represent random variables and a distance metric for machine learning algorithms. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses experiments on synthetic datasets, which could fall under statistics (cs.ST) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the example of clustering financial time series could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI).
